model.dek: Before you watch the Oscars this Sunday, look back through award-worthy celebrity spaces from the pages of *AD*

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-jennifer-aniston-jennifer-aniston-07-lanai.jpg
items.caption: In __[Jennifer Aniston’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2010/jennifer-aniston-home-slideshow)__ Beverly Hills home, travertine floors warm the lanai, which can be enclosed with a bronze chain-mail curtain. The fabric on the love seat and chairs in the foreground is from Holly Hunt, as are the pillow fabrics. Chella fabric covers the Shadley-designed chairs near the fireplace.

items.title: dam-images-decor-2015-02-celebrity-spaces-02-diane-keaton.jpg
items.caption: Monterey furniture served as __[Diane Keaton’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2008/diane-keaton-home-slideshow)__ inspiration for the table she designed for the office—once an open-air loggia—in her Beverly Hills residence.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2013-cindy-crawford-and-rande-gerber-cindy-crawford-rande-gerber-14-george-clooney-master-bath.jpg
items.caption: __[George Clooney’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2013/george-clooney-cindy-crawford-rande-gerber-mexico-baja-houses-slideshow)__master bath terrace, shaded by a parota brise-soleil, has a travertine Jacuzzi lined in blue mosaic tiles. The side table is by Tucker Robbins, and the lanterns are by Casamidy.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-ellen-degeneres-ellen-degeneres-portia-de-rossi-beverly-hills-home-03-entrance-hall.jpg
items.caption: In [__Ellen Degeneres__and __Portia de Rossi’s______](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2011/ellen-degeneres-and-portia-de-rossi-beverly-hills-home-slideshow) home, a Ping-Pong table by Argentine artist Rirkrit Tiravanija makes a playful statement in the entrance hall, which features a Spanish Colonial bench from Lief and a Serge Mouille chandelier; the 19th-century Agra carpet is from the Melrose Project.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2014-celebrity-outdoor-entertaining-celebrities-outdoor-spaces-05-patrick-dempsey.jpg
items.caption: At the Frank Gehry–designed Malibu home of actor __[Patrick Dempsey](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2014/patrick-dempsey-frank-gehry-malibu-california-home-slideshow)__ and his family, a metal-framed wicker canopy shades an outdoor dining space created by Shrader Design.

items.title: dam-images-homes-2010-05-gerard_butler-gerard-butler-06-kitchen.jpg
items.caption: Actor __[Gerard Butler](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2010/gerard-butler-new-york-city-home-slideshow)__worked with architect Alexander Gorlin and film designer Elvis Restaino on his 3,300-square-foot loft in Manhattan. The kitchen’s cabinetry and backsplash were fashioned from leftover flooring materials.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2014-jane-fonda-jane-fonda-new-mexico-ranch-06-dining-area.jpg
items.caption: A 1922 painting by Alson Skinner Clark overlooks the dining area on __[Jane Fonda’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2014/jane-fonda-forked-lightning-ranch-new-mexico-slideshow)__New Mexico ranch; the table is set with two pairs of Spanish Colonial candlesticks, the smaller of which was owned by the fashion icon Millicent Rogers, one of Fonda’s relatives.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-julianne-moore-julianne-moore-garden-new-york-05.jpg
items.caption: The painted trim of __[Julianne Moore’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2012/julianne-moore-home-garden-new-york-slideshow)__ 1905 Manhattan house is complemented by matte-black accents found throughout the garden; the window box is planted with English ivy, and a purple sweet potato vine adds a splash of color at the foot of the stairs.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2013-will-ferrell-will-ferrell-03-kitchen.jpg
items.caption: The open kitchen in __[Will Ferrell’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2013/will-ferrell-manhattan-loft-apartment-slideshow)__ Manhattan loft is equipped with a Sub-Zero refrigerator, Kallista sink fittings, and BassamFellows stools from Design Within Reach; at right is a Lichtenstein print. In the dining area, Tejo Remy light fixtures are suspended above a vintage Paul T. Frankl dining table; artisan Tanya Aguiñiga covered the Eames chairs with blue felt, and the flower images are by Donald Sultan.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2014-celebrity-outdoor-entertaining-celebrities-outdoor-spaces-09-cindy-crawford-rande-gerber.jpg
items.caption: On __[Cindy Crawford and Rande Gerber’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2013/george-clooney-cindy-crawford-rande-gerber-mexico-baja-houses-slideshow)__ pool terrace in Los Cabos, Mexico, Christian Liaigre director’s chairs surround a custom-made dining table; the Gibson guitar was a gift from Kid Rock, a frequent guest.

items.title: dam-images-celebrity-homes-2014-julianna-margulies-julianna-margulies-01-manhattan-living-room.jpg
items.caption: The living area in __[Julianna Margulies’s](http://www.architecturaldigest.com/celebrity-homes/2014/julianna-margulies-vicente-wolf-manhattan-apartment-slideshow)__ Manhattan apartment is anchored by a sofa covered in a Larsen fabric. The African carved post and Portuguese Colonial candlesticks standing at the window are from VW Home, as are the Burmese side table and the hand sculpture; the lounge chair is by B&B Italia, and the carpet is by Doris Leslie Blau.
